abstain.def: restrain oneself from doing or enjoying something

apathy.def: an absence of emotion or enthusiasm

ascetic.def: avoiding physical pleasures and living a simple life, often for religious reasons
a person who follows an ascetic life

belligerent.def: characteristic of one eager to fight, hostile and aggressive

circumvent.def: to avoid something, especially cleverly or illegally

construe.def: interpret (a word or action) in a particular way

contrive.def: to pull off a plan or scheme, usually through skill or trickery

derivative.def: imitative of the work of another artist, writer, etc., and usually disapproved of for that reason

disaffected.def: dissatisfied, especially with people in authority or a system of control

eclectic.def: comprising of a variety of styles or ideas

eminent.def: standing above others in quality or position

ephemeral.def: lasting for a very short time

forlorn.def: pitifully sad and abandoned or lonely
(of an aim or endeavour) unlikely to succeed or be fulfilled

frustrate.def: prevent (a plan or action) from succeeding
cause (someone) to feel upset or annoyed from being unable to achieve something

guileless.def: devoid of guile; innocent and without deception

heretic.def: a person who holds unorthodox opinions in any field (not merely religion)

heresy.def: belief or opinion contrary to orthodox religious doctrine or what is generally accepted

iconoclastic.def: a person who strongly opposes generally accepted beliefs and traditions

incongruous.def: not in harmony or with the surroundings or other aspects of something

ingratiate.def: bring oneself into favour with someone by flattering or trying to please them

insidious.def: proceeding in a gradual, subtle way, but with harmful effects

itinerant.def: travelling from place to place, usually to work for a short period

jingoism.def: extreme patriotism, especially in the form of aggressive or warlike policy

jubilant.def: feeling or expressing great happiness, especially because of triumph or success

juxtapose.def: place side by side for contrast

languid.def: (of a person, manner, or gesture) showing disinclination for physical exertion or effort; slow and relaxed

magnanimous.def: generous or forgiving, especially towards a rival or less powerful person

mollify.def: to make someone angry less angry

negligible.def: so small as to be not worth considering

panache.def: flamboyant confidence of style or manner that makes people admire you

precocious.def: (of a child) showing mental development or achievement at an earlier age than is usual

pundit.def: an expert in a particular subject who is frequently called upon to give their opinion

rudimentary.def: involving or limited to basic principles, relating to an undeveloped or basic form

scholar.def: a person who is highly educated or has an aptitude for study

soporific.def: tending to induce drowsiness or sleep

staunch.def: very loyal and committed in attitude

subsume.def: to include (something or someone) as part of a larger group

tantamount.def: equivalent in seriousness to (usually something bad)

tenacious.def: tending to keep a firm hold of something

treacherous.def: (of conditions) presenting hidden or unpredictable dangers

unorthodox.def: contrary to what is usual, traditional, or accepted

vehement.def: showing strong feeling or forceful energy

vilify.def: spread negative information about (someone or something)
